## ðŸ”¹ Popular Raspberry Pi HATs

**Raspberry Pi HATs** (Hardware Attached on Top) are add-on boards that conform to specific design standards, allowing for seamless integration with Raspberry Pi boards. Here are some commonly used HATs:

### 1. **Sense HAT**

Designed for environmental sensing and data logging.

- **Sensors:** Temperature, Humidity, Barometric Pressure, Gyroscope, Accelerometer, Magnetometer
- **Display:** 8Ã—8 RGB LED matrix
- **Additional Features:** Joystick for user input

### 2. **Motor HAT**

Ideal for robotics and motor control applications.

- **Motor Control:** Dual H-Bridge for controlling DC motors
- **PWM Channels:** Multiple channels for precise motor speed control
- **Power Supply:** Supports external power sources for motors ([Raspberry Pi announces a $7 Pico 2 with built-in Wi-Fi](https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/25/24305455/raspberry-pi-pico-2-w-wi-fi-wireless-microcontroller?utm_source=chatgpt.com), [RP2040](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RP2040?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

### 3. **Audio HAT**

Enhances audio capabilities of the Raspberry Pi.

- **Audio Output:** High-quality DAC for stereo output
- **Connectivity:** 3.5mm audio jack, RCA outputs
- **Additional Features:** Some models include microphones for audio input ([Raspberry Pi Pico W and Pico WH - Thingbits India](https://www.thingbits.in/products/raspberry-pi-pico-w?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

---

These HATs expand the functionality of Raspberry Pi boards, enabling a wide range of projects from environmental monitoring to robotics and multimedia applications.
